@node "Description" "Description"

@{jcenter}
@{b}Disciption@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
With this tool you can setup the bandwidth control of your Zyxel ISDN-TA.

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

@{b}Installation@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
Copy the Drawer in the language drawer wherever you want. It's nessessary that you copy the full drawer in the language drawer.@{line}
@{line}
After that, you have to modify the Init-String of all programs, you want to use the settings made by this program.@{line}
Remove all entries like &Fx, Zx, JAxx, JSxx, KAxx, KSxx and CEx. After that add Z1 in the string.@{line}
Example:@{line}
Old string: AT@{u}&F@{uu}&O2B40&DO@{line}
Change to: AT@{u}Z1@{uu}&O2B40&D0@{line}
@{line}
After that all programs using init: ATZ1 are using the settings made by the ZyxelControl.@{line}

@endnode

@node "Problems" "Problems"

@{b}Problems@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
@{b}1@{ub}@{line}
It's possible that the program shows you more than one error. This is nessessary because it's possible that more than one reasson ist responsable that the program doesn't work.@{line}

@endnode


@node "Errors" "Errors"

@{b}Error messages@{ub}@{line}
@{line}
@{u}SerialManaer not found!@{uu}@{line}
For multible and shared device communication, the SerialManager is used. It's needed that this tool is located in the ZyelControl drawer.@{line}
This message says you, that this tool isn't found in this drawer or the program can't open this tool.@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Communication failt!@{uu}@{line}
This message shows up, if the SerialManager is loaded, but the communication to this tool doesn't work. It's also possible, that the SerialManager is allready closed and the program tries to communicate to the SerialManager.@{line}
This message says you, that the serialport is opened by another program, wich doesn't share the serialport.@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Can't speak to device!@{uu}@{line}
This message shows up, if the SerialManager is loaded, but the communication to this tool doesn't work. It's also possible, that the SerialManager is allready closed and the program tries to communicate to the SerialManager.@{line}
This message says you, that the serialport is opened by another program, wich doesn't share the serialport.@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Modem is not responding!@{uu}@{line}
This means, that the SerialManager and the program can send messages to the device, but the device doesn't answer.@{line}
This message says you, that the modem doesn't answer, there is no modem connected on this device, or the modems answer is irracional.@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Can't open device!@{uu}@{line}
This shows up, if the device doesn't exist.@{line}
This messages says you, that you have to enter a vaild device.@{line}

@endnode


